@node Release @value{PACKAGE}-@value{VERSION}
@unnumberedsubsec Major changes for release @value{PACKAGE}-@value{VERSION}
@cindex release @value{PACKAGE}-@value{VERSION}

This is the fourth separate release from @cite{The OpenSS7 Project} of the
@cite{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}} package.  The package provides components that were
previously part of the @file{strss7} package.

With OpenSS7 Master Package release @file{openss-0.9.2.D}, the Channel
components were separated from the @file{strss7} package and placed in this
package.  Not all of the Channel components previously part of the @file{strss7}
package have been strapped into this release.  Components will be re-validated
against @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS} on a module-by-module and driver-by-driver
basis.@footnote{Note that no component in this package can be supported by
@cite{LiS}: @cite{LiS} is simply too slow to allow these drivers to acheive any
degree of efficiency necessary for proper operation.} See @file{TODO} in the
release, or @refman{Schedule}, for more information about the release schedule.

This is the fourth pre-alpha release for @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS} and is an
optional part of the OpenSS7 Master Package (as of @file{openss7-0.9.2.D}).
This release is a maintenance release providing support for recent distributions
and tool chains.

Major features since the last public release are as follows:

@itemize -
@item
Added Open Media Gatway project document.

@item
Kernel module license made explicit "GPL v2".  And then changed back to "GPL".

@item
Added @file{mx-pmod} and @file{ch-pmod} STREAMS modules and manual pages (@manref{ch-pmod(4)} and
@manref{mx-pmod(4)}).  These STREAMS modules provide the CH and MX interfaces to a STREAMS-based
pipe acting as a channel or multiplex connection for testing and complex interconnection of channels
and multiplexes.

@item
64-bit corrections to the CHI header file, @file{sys/chi.h}.

@item
Updated documentation.

@item
License upgrade to GPL Version 3.

@item
Fix for freezestr() and unfreezestr() on 2.4 kernels.

@item
Ability to strap out major documentation build and installation primarily for
embedded targets.

@item
Improvements to common build process for embedded and cross-compile targets.

@item
Support for flex 2.5.33  in maintainer mode.

@end itemize

@emph{This is a public pre-alpha release of the package.  Please see
@file{README-alpha} in the release or @refman{Maturity}.}

This package is currently incomplete.  It is being released as a reference point
for the community.  If you are interested in completion of this package, contact
@email{info@@openss7.com}.

As with other OpenSS7 releases, this release configures, compiles, installs and
builds RPMs and DEBs for a wide range of Linux 2.4 and 2.6 RPM- and DPKG-based
distributions, and can be used on production kernels without patching or
recompiling the kernel.

This package is publicly released under the @cite{GNU General Public License
