@node Release @value{PACKAGE}-0.9.2.1
@unnumberedsubsec Major changes for release @value{PACKAGE}-0.9.2.1
@cindex release @value{PACKAGE}-0.9.2.1

This is the first separate release from @cite{The OpenSS7 Project} of the
@cite{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}} package.  The package provides components that
were previously part of the @file{strss7} package.

With OpenSS7 Master Package release @file{openss-0.9.2.D}, the Channel
components were separated from the @file{strss7} package and placed in this
package.  Not all of the Channel components previously part of the
@file{strss7} package have been strapped into this release.  Components will
be re-validated against @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS} on a module-by-module and
driver-by-driver basis.@footnote{Note that no component in this package can
be supported by @cite{LiS}: @cite{LiS} is simply too slow to allow these
drivers to acheive any degree of efficiency necessary for proper operation.}
See @file{TODO} in the release, or @refman{Schedule}, for more information
about the release schedule.

In this initial release, the major component first available is the V401P
channel driver.  In contrast to the X400P-SS7 driver from the @cite{strss7}
package, this driver provides enhanced support for audio channels and the
basis for Zaptel integration.  The release also contains a set of pushable
modules for use with the channel driver that provide HDLC/DAEDR capabilities
for channels.  These components do not as yet have validation test suites.

Subsequent releases in 1Q 2007 will include the additional components
necessary for Media Gateway switching support.

This is the initial pre-alpha release for @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS} and is an
optional part of the OpenSS7 Master Package (as of @file{openss7-0.9.2.D}).
This release is also the initial public release.

